{"author":{"id":"566a90f06ed91cad74642413b9b85c80c6102ef8f51c1ae55157b616944bedd5"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1652087275,"nonce":"DAT8F4KDoh+r/h+uKbsMVbpurN0=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOAW4Y0s5JR0ZV","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/4555","origin":"github"},"title":"[SPAdes]--cov-cutoff option with user specific value isn't parsed correctly by the wrapper","message":"Hello IUC team,\n\nThere is an issue with the SPAdes tool's wrapper. When the --cov-cutoff option is set with a  user specific value, \"value\" is written in the command line instead of the actual value pick by the user in the additional form field.  Command line look like : `--cov-cutoff value ` and SPades crash with the following error : ` error: argument --cov-cutoff: wrong value value (should be a positive float number, or 'auto', or 'off')` .  It does work with the default value ('off') and the 'auto' value too  because the wrapper does this : \n` ## parameter\n    --cov-cutoff $cov_cond.cov_cutoff` ,\n\nThat 'cov_cond' parameter is set in the macro xml : \n\n` \u003cxml name=\"covcutoff\"\u003e\n        \u003cconditional name=\"cov_cond\"\u003e\n            \u003cparam argument=\"--cov-cutoff\" type=\"select\" label=\"Set coverage cutoff option\" help=\"When set to 'auto' SPAdes automatically computes coverage threshold using conservative strategy\"\u003e\n                \u003coption value=\"off\"\u003eOff\u003c/option\u003e\n                \u003coption value=\"auto\"\u003eAuto\u003c/option\u003e\n                \u003coption value=\"value\"\u003eUser specific\u003c/option\u003e\n            \u003c/param\u003e\n            \u003cwhen value=\"off\"/\u003e\n            \u003cwhen value=\"auto\"/\u003e\n            \u003cwhen value=\"value\"\u003e\n                \u003cparam name=\"manual\" type=\"float\" min=\"0\" value=\"\" label=\"Set value\"/\u003e\n            \u003c/when\u003e\n        \u003c/conditional\u003e\n    \u003c/xml\u003e`\n\nSo in the 'User specific case' ,  the parameter should be set to $cov_cond.manual, or the conditional should be updated to change the value of the 'con_cutoff' dropdown instead.","files":null}]}